http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Pick up your ultimate guide to the Olympics!\", \"from\": 723, \"to\": 767, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Going for Gold provides the day-by-day rundown of what's on and when.\", \"from\": 768, \"to\": 837, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Clickhereto buy.\", \"from\": 838, \"to\": 854, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Adam Peaty admitted that he has gone through the \\\"worst week of my life\\\" physically after he had to pull out of the 4x100m medley relay final.\", \"from\": 856, \"to\": 998, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 856, \"end\": 866, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adam_Peaty\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Adam Peaty\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adam_Peaty\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adam_Peaty\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The British three-time Olympic gold medallist caughtCovid-19 while in the athletes' village and while he has been back in the pool, struggled throughout his bout of illness.\", \"from\": 1000, \"to\": 1173, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It's probably the worst week of my life in terms of how my body is, and that's no exaggeration,\\\" he admitted.\", \"from\": 1175, \"to\": 1285, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Everything's come at once.\", \"from\": 1287, \"to\": 1314, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Since Covid, it's just every day waking up with a different thing.\", \"from\": 1315, \"to\": 1381, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The medical team's been brilliant.\", \"from\": 1383, \"to\": 1418, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I think it's just a victory getting on that start block there.\", \"from\": 1419, \"to\": 1481, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Hopefully, that'll give my body a nice little push for tomorrow.\\\"\", \"from\": 1482, \"to\": 1547, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Julien Alfred is pretty sure that St. Lucia will party long into the night after she secured her country's first-ever Olympic gold medal.\", \"from\": 1549, \"to\": 1686, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1587, \"end\": 1592, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Characters_of_Devil_May_Cry\", \"score\": 0.9955488816815922, \"rank\": 0.004471014916678539, \"text\": \"Lucia\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Characters_of_Devil_May_Cry\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Characters_of_Devil_May_Cry\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She blitzed the 100-metre race and won at a canter, making history that will be celebrated back home.\", \"from\": 1688, \"to\": 1789, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I am sure they are having a time,\\\" Alfred told theBBC.\", \"from\": 1791, \"to\": 1846, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Playing music, celebrating, drinking beers.\", \"from\": 1847, \"to\": 1891, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It feels amazing [to have won gold and a first Olympic medal for St Lucia].\", \"from\": 1893, \"to\": 1969, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1959, \"end\": 1967, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saint_Lucia\", \"score\": 0.9999999988076524, \"rank\": 1.1609940171004477e-09, \"text\": \"St Lucia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saint_Lucia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saint_Lucia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I am going through the motions right now.\", \"from\": 1970, \"to\": 2011, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It has not sunk in as yet.\", \"from\": 2012, \"to\": 2038, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I had to go out there, trust myself, trust my coach and most importantly trust God.\\\"\", \"from\": 2040, \"to\": 2125, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Julien Alfred has become the first-ever athlete from St Lucia to win a gold medal, doing so in none other than the women's 100-metre race.\", \"from\": 2127, \"to\": 2265, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2180, \"end\": 2188, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saint_Lucia\", \"score\": 0.9999999988076524, \"rank\": 1.1609940171004477e-09, \"text\": \"St Lucia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saint_Lucia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saint_Lucia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"An impressive10.72 seconds was enough to beat out second-placed Sha'Carri Richardson, with Melissa Jefferson third and Team GB's Daryll Neita in fourth.\", \"from\": 2267, \"to\": 2419, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2331, \"end\": 2351, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sha'Carri_Richardson\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Sha'Carri Richardson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sha'Carri_Richardson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sha'Carri_Richardson\"}, {\"begin\": 2358, \"end\": 2375, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lizzo\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Melissa Jefferson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lizzo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lizzo\"}, {\"begin\": 2386, \"end\": 2393, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.3485674604637953e-22, \"text\": \"Team GB\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\"}, {\"begin\": 2396, \"end\": 2408, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daryll_Neita\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Daryll Neita\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daryll_Neita\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daryll_Neita\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Alfred won by 0.15s, a considerable distance, to kickstart parties back home and the 180,000 people in St. Lucia now have an Olympic gold medal.\", \"from\": 2421